# Per-Dockerfile ignore (BuildKit). Applied when building with
# `-f apps/api/Dockerfile`. Takes precedence over the root .dockerignore.

# Workspace members not needed for the API image. The Dockerfile only
# COPYs the api + types package.json files, so the rest never reaches the
# build context — but explicit exclusion keeps the context smaller and
# guards against accidental future COPYs.
apps/web
packages/cli
packages/create-ruleshub
packages/ruleshub-kit

# Test artifacts (image runs only built src/)
apps/api/test
**/*.spec.ts
**/*.e2e-spec.ts

# Caches and local clutter
**/node_modules
**/dist
**/.next
**/.turbo
**/coverage
**/*.tsbuildinfo
**/*.log

# Repo metadata
.git
.github
**/CLAUDE.md
**/README.md
**/audit.md
**/Dockerfile*

# Local env files — never bake into images
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example
